// 1. Sessionize the web log by IP. Sessionize = aggregrate all page hits by visitor/IP during a session.
val inactive_window = lit(10*60)
val session_data = data.select($"*", lag("timestamp", 1).over(Window.partitionBy("client_ip").orderBy("timestamp")).as("prev_timestamp"))
              .withColumn("next_session", when((unix_timestamp($"timestamp") - unix_timestamp($"prev_timestamp")) >= inactive_window, lit(1)).otherwise(lit(0)))
              .withColumn("session", sum($"next_session").over(Window.partitionBy($"client_ip").orderBy($"client_ip", $"timestamp")))
              .withColumn("session_id", concat($"client_ip", lit("_"), $"session"))
              .drop("next_session", "prev_timestamp")
// sessionized_data.write.parquet(output_path+"Sessionized_Weblog.parquet")
z.show(session_data.select("timestamp", "elb", "client:port", "client_ip", "session", "session_id", "backend:port", "request_processing_time", "backend_processing_time", "response_processing_time",
               "elb_status_code", "backend_status_code", "received_bytes", "sent_bytes", "request", "url", "user_agent", "ssl_cipher", "ssl_protocol"), 8)

// Drop user sessions with only first session and one record in the data
val session_count = session_data.groupBy($"session_id").count()
val single_record_sessions = session_count.filter($"count" === 1).select($"session_id").rdd.map(r => r(0)).collect.toList
val sessionized_data = session_data.filter(!(($"session_id".isin(single_record_sessions : _*)) && ($"session" === 0)))

// 2. Determine the average session time
val session_length_data = sessionized_data.groupBy($"session_id").agg((unix_timestamp(max($"timestamp")) - unix_timestamp(min($"timestamp"))) as "session_length")
                                          .withColumn("client_ip", split($"session_id", "_")(0))
                                          .withColumn("session", split($"session_id", "_")(1).cast(IntegerType))
session_length_data.select(avg($"session_length").as("Average session time across all users (in seconds)")).show()

// Part-2
// 1. Predict the expected load (requests/second) in the next minute
val tmp_0 = sessionized_data.withColumn("Time", date_format($"timestamp", "y-M-d HH:mm").cast("timestamp"))
                            .withColumn("response_processing_time", when(($"response_processing_time" === lit("-1")), lit(0)))
                            .groupBy($"Time").agg(mean($"sent_bytes") as "sent_bytes", mean($"received_bytes") as "received_bytes", 
                                                  mean($"response_processing_time") as "response_processing_time", countDistinct($"session_id") as "sessions_active", count($"*")/lit(60) as "Load")
                                                      
val tmp_1 = tmp_0.withColumn("Prev_sent_bytes", lag("sent_bytes", 1, 0).over(Window.orderBy($"Time")))
               .withColumn("Prev_received_bytes", lag("received_bytes", 1, 0).over(Window.orderBy($"Time")))
               .withColumn("Prev_response_processing_time", lag("response_processing_time", 1, 0).over(Window.orderBy($"Time")))
               .withColumn("Prev_sessions_active", lag("sessions_active", 1, 0).over(Window.orderBy($"Time")))
               .withColumn("Prev_Load", lag("Load", 1, 0).over(Window.orderBy($"Time")))
               .withColumn("Minute", date_format($"Time", "mm").cast(IntegerType))
               .drop("sent_bytes", "received_bytes", "response_processing_time", "sessions_active")
               
val (minp, maxp) = tmp_1.select(min($"Time").cast("bigint"), max($"Time".cast("bigint")))
                        .as[(Long, Long)]
                        .first
                        
val step: Long = 1 * 60

val reference = spark.range((minp / step) * step, ((maxp / step) + 1) * step, step)
                     .select($"id".cast("timestamp").alias("Time"))
val total_size = reference.count.toInt
val load_data = reference.join(tmp_1, Seq("Time"), "leftouter").na.fill(0, Seq("Load", "Prev_sent_bytes", "Prev_received_bytes", "Prev_response_processing_time", "Prev_sessions_active", "Prev_Load", "Minute")).sort(asc("Time"))
                         .withColumn("index", row_number().over(Window.orderBy("Time")))
load_data.show(8, false)
z.show(load_data.select($"Time", $"Load"), total_size)

val build_data = load_data.where($"index" < 666)
val val_data = load_data.where($"index" >= 666 && $"index" < 888)
val test_data = load_data.where($"index" >= 888)

import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler

// Index features

  .setInputCols(Array("Prev_sent_bytes", "Prev_received_bytes", "Prev_response_processing_time", "Prev_sessions_active", "Prev_Load", "Minute"))
  .setOutputCol("assembledFeatures")

// Build Data
val buildData = assembler
    .transform(build_data)
    .select(
        "assembledFeatures",
        "Load"
    )

// Validation Data
val valData = assembler
    .transform(val_data)
    .select(
        "assembledFeatures",
        "Load"
    )
    
// Test Data
val testData = assembler
    .transform(test_data)
    .select(
        "assembledFeatures",
        "Load"
    )
